'Bigg Boss OTT 3' Under Fire for Alleged Vulgarity: Politician Demands Action Against Armaan Malik

The makers and contestants of 'Bigg Boss OTT Season 3' are facing legal trouble after Shiv Sena leader Manisha Kayande filed a complaint with the Mumbai Police. Manisha Kayande has demanded strict action against both the makers and contestants of the show, alleging that they have been spreading vulgarity. The controversy escalated when a clip, purportedly showing Armaan and Kritika in an intimate moment, went viral online. JioCinema, however, has officially denied the allegations, stating that the video has been doctored. They have vowed to initiate legal action against those responsible for creating and distributing such defamatory content. Meanwhile, Armaan has become the center of attention as the most talked-about contestant from 'Bigg Boss OTT 3', sparking debates over his admission of being married to both Payal and Kritika Malik.

Rhea Chakraborty Opens Up About Life Post SSR's Death: 'I enter a room and I can polarise it!'

Bollywood diva Rhea recently discussed life after SSR's death, launching her podcast with Sushmita Sen as the inaugural guest. In the debut episode, she candidly addressed her personal life and how the public perceives her since the incident. Rhea shared her unique perspective, describing her ability to polarize a room, where some view her as controversial while others see her as resilient and courageous. She humorously recounted how this dynamic plays out in various settings like the dentist's clinic, gym, and airport, emphasizing that public opinion doesn't affect her.

672 views | 2 days ago

Hardik Pandya and Ananya Panday's Dance Video Causes Online Stir

After the surprising announcement of Natasa Stankovic and Hardik Pandya's separation on July 18, the internet turned its attention to matchmaking between Ananya Panday and Hardik. Meanwhile, a dance video featuring the actress and cricketer from the Ambani wedding garnered significant attention online. Following Hardik & Natasa's joint statement on Instagram confirming their decision to part ways, the internet was flooded with expressions of sadness and broken heart emojis. Despite the emotional aftermath, cyberspace seemed to offer solace quicker than reality as shattered fans found comfort in Hardik's video from the Ambani wedding. Some eagle-eyed netizens discovered clips showing Hardik and Ananya together, prompting widespread discussion.

1456 views | 4 days ago

Chirag Paswan on Kangana Ranaut: 'She Isn't Politically Correct, and That's Her Strength'

Union Minister Chirag Paswan recently opened up about his memorable 'Jab We Met' moment with Kangana Ranaut in Parliament during an interview. He discussed their bond and remarked, 'Kangana isn't politically correct, but that's her USP.' When asked if he would offer tips to Kangana for her speech, Chirag shared his thoughts. He also provided insights into his time in Bollywood and addressed the nepotism debate, acknowledging his own background in it. Notably, Kangana and Chirag starred together in the 2011 film 'Mile Na Mile Hum'. On the film front, Kangana is set to appear in 'Emergency', which is scheduled to hit theaters on September 6.
